# Stripe Webhook Configuration
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Use Stripe CLI: stripe listen --forward-to localhost:3000/api/stripe/webhook
# 2. Copy the webhook signing secret to STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
#
# NGROK DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Go to Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks
# 2. Add endpoint: https://your-subdomain.ngrok-free.dev/api/stripe/webhook
# 3. Select events: checkout.session.completed, checkout.session.expired
# 4. Copy the webhook secret to STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# 5. Update NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your ngrok URL
#
# PRODUCTION:
# 1. Go to Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks
# 2. Add endpoint: https://yourdomain.com/api/stripe/webhook
# 3. Select events: checkout.session.completed, checkout.session.expired
# 4. Copy the webhook secret to STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# Supabase Setup Instructions
# 1. Create new project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Go to Settings → API
# 3. Copy Project URL to NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
# 4. Copy anon public key to NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 5. Copy service_role secret key to SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# 6. Run the SQL above to create transactions table

# Plausible Analytics Setup
# 1. Sign up at https://plausible.io
# 2. Add your domain
# 3. Copy domain to NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN

# Exchange Rate API (Optional)
# 1. Sign up at https://exchangerate.host (free tier available)
# 2. Or use any other exchange rate API
# 3. Update lib/fees.ts to use your API if needed
